commitResults.messageBody:
There are several methods that are incomplete in both classes.

Updating both classes by fleshing out those incomplete methods improves their functionality.

Moving forward, both classes will be updated again to incorporate classes added into the source code by team members, to reflect the actual working version for both classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update fields and methods in Task and TaskList classes
commitResults.messageBody:
There are fields and several methods that are incomplete in both classes due to missing classes. Name class in the task package has the same name as the Name class in the person package.

Updating both classes by fleshing out those incomplete fields and methods improves their functionality and brings them closer to their actual working versions. Additionally, changing the name of the class to TaskName better reflects its purpose and prevents confusion.

Moving forward, Task and TaskList classes will be closely monitored and updated to fit the purposes of our final product.

There are no exception handlers for processes that deal with tasks.

Adding task-specific exceptions helps to maintain the normal, desired flow of the program even when unexpected events occur, preventing unwanted outcomes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Allow filtering of tasks by deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
Users are currently only able to view the list of tasks without being able to modify it based on any criteria.

Filtering tasks by deadline will allow users to quickly identify the specific tasks that they are looking for based on the input deadline.

Moving forward, more functionalities will be added to provide users with greater flexibility and control over the task list.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix style errors due to import ordering

commitResults.messageBody:
After filtering, the current function displays a list of tasks with deadline that must be equal to the input deadline. However, this leaves out tasks with deadlines that come before the input deadline.

This change allows the user to see a list of tasks with deadlines specific to and before the input deadline for greater clarity.

commitResults.messageTitle: Sync fitler functions into a single command
commitResults.messageBody:
Commands to filter tasks by their categories and deadlines are currently separate.

Syncing both functionalities into a single command improves overall cohesiveness of the program as they're both trying to accomplish the same outcome, which is to filter the task list. This reduces confusion as well on the users' end, as they need not go through the hassle of remembering two functions when they essentially both do similar things.

Moving forward, the filter function will receive updates such that tasks can also be filtered by their names, descriptions, priorities, assigned person(s), and statuses.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix style errors due to Javadoc comments and unused imports
Fix a bug in filtering by TaskDeadline
commitResults.messageBody:
Filter function does not allow a date input that is earlier than the current date.

While this may be correct and intuitive for creating tasks, as deadlines should only occur in the future, it is not so for the input argument for filtering tasks by date. This change allows users to filter their tasks with deadlines that are older than the current date.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix style errors due to unused imports
Allow finding of tasks using keywords
commitResults.messageBody:
Users are currently only able to view, filter, and sort the list of tasks, without being able to look for a specific task.

Finding tasks using keywords will allow users to quickly identify the specific tasks that they are looking for.

Currently, if a Task is assigned to no one, the message displayed to the user reads: "Assigned to: null".

However, this should be abstracted from the user. Hence, instead of null, the new message displays: "Assigned to: None".
